<P>ON the left Bank of the River <HI>Spir|nazza</HI> which <HI>Strabo</HI> calls <HI>Pami&s;|&s;us,</HI> Ptolomey <HI>Pami&s;&s;us,</HI> Niger <HI>Stronio,</HI> and Giovio <HI>Tifoo;</HI> on the hanging of a Hill lyes the Fortre&s;s of <HI>Calamata</HI> of a large extent, by <HI>Baudrand</HI> called <HI>Thelame, Theramme, Thuria</HI> and <HI>Abia,</HI> from the Nur&s;e of <HI>Helles</HI> one of <HI>Hercu|les</HI>'s Sons<HI>:</HI> Its Situation is in an open place in the Province of <HI>Belvedere,</HI> it is well Peopled, and though the Town
